pageContext.claim: “If Hillary Clinton got elected, instead of 4.1 up -- and each point is $3.5 trillion and 10 million jobs. When I took it over, it was at 1, and it was going to be down -- it was going down.”
pageContext.analysis: The gross domestic product grew at an annual rate of 1.5 percent in 2016 -- and 2.3 percent in 2017. A president only affects such economic trends at the margins, especially at the start of an administration.
